1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:04,980
Hey, guys! We’re almost there.
Look at that. Welcome!

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:06,258
Welcome, welcome!

3
00:00:06,283 --> 00:00:10,365
So guys, don’t miss our
grand reopening, okay?

4
00:00:10,390 --> 00:00:12,972
Yes, until the next episode. See you!

5
00:00:12,997 --> 00:00:14,007
Bye-bye!

6
00:00:14,105 --> 00:00:15,105
Bye!

7
00:00:16,535 --> 00:00:17,234
Beautiful!

8
00:00:17,259 --> 00:00:18,963
- Nice one, nice one!
- Perfect, perfect, perfect!

9
00:00:18,987 --> 00:00:23,127
Hey, our newly improved
bakery is almost ready!

10
00:00:23,411 --> 00:00:24,411
That’s right!

11
00:00:24,490 --> 00:00:29,569
And it’s all because of my
beautiful and handsome grandkids!

12
00:00:30,550 --> 00:00:33,890
- Wow, Lola!
- Lola, thank you so much.

13
00:00:33,915 --> 00:00:34,408
Right?

14
00:00:34,439 --> 00:00:36,605
- Thank you, Lola!
- You’ve done so much.

15
00:00:36,630 --> 00:00:39,155
Yeah, your help has been incredible.

16
00:00:39,926 --> 00:00:41,979
Well, we really appreciate it, you know.

17
00:00:42,514 --> 00:00:44,594
Of course, we couldn’t
have done it without you guys.

18
00:00:45,027 --> 00:00:46,366
Family, right?

19
00:00:46,608 --> 00:00:50,268
The Pers! We’re the Pers!

20
00:00:52,022 --> 00:00:54,635
Is that Uncle Iskineport?

21
00:00:57,548 --> 00:00:58,835
What are they up to?

22
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:01,944
Psst, hey!

23
00:01:01,969 --> 00:01:04,877
Hey! Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey! Don’t do that!

24
00:01:04,902 --> 00:01:07,749
What are you doing? Why are you doing that?

25
00:01:07,774 --> 00:01:09,562
Are you sure that’s clean?

26
00:01:09,705 --> 00:01:10,443
Mmm!

27
00:01:10,468 --> 00:01:12,508
Well, it’s such a waste.

28
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:14,147
The customers left it.

29
00:01:14,306 --> 00:01:18,840
There are so many hungry people, and they
leave delicious bread like this behind?

30
00:01:18,974 --> 00:01:20,901
Exactly, wasting blessings!

31
00:01:21,031 --> 00:01:24,358
Especially now that
our food is even better!

32
00:01:25,097 --> 00:01:26,110
You know what,

33
00:01:26,936 --> 00:01:30,643
since we’ve been
working all day anyway,

34
00:01:30,668 --> 00:01:35,190
I’ll just prepare snacks for everyone
so you won’t do things like that!

35
00:01:35,215 --> 00:01:36,649
Wow, yes!

36
00:01:39,022 --> 00:01:41,112
- Are we included?
- Are we?

37
00:01:41,137 --> 00:01:44,565
- Aren’t we all family?
- Of course!

38
00:01:44,745 --> 00:01:45,745
Yes!

39
00:01:48,970 --> 00:01:51,615
Kuya Iskineport, why are
you throwing away our food?!

40
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,423
What did you do there?!

41
00:01:52,448 --> 00:01:53,969
I threw it, like this!

42
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:56,939
Tito, you clean that up, okay?!

43
00:02:57,939 --> 00:02:59,879
Alright, alright, okay!

44
00:03:00,445 --> 00:03:02,792
- Hey! We made it by God’s grace!
- Thank God!

45
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:08,475
- Whew! That was intense!
- Kuya, you’re so happy!

46
00:03:09,037 --> 00:03:12,110
This is heavy!
We managed to pull it off, though!

47
00:03:12,135 --> 00:03:16,537
Here, we bought all the supplies.

48
00:03:18,610 --> 00:03:20,444
We almost had an accident!

49
00:03:20,471 --> 00:03:22,492
We went so far, to Ilocos!

50
00:03:22,792 --> 00:03:24,618
Then we nearly had an accident here!

51
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,580
Here’s everything we bought.

52
00:03:26,605 --> 00:03:28,128
Oh, and here’s the receipt.

53
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:31,689
Were you praying we’d fail again?

54
00:03:32,553 --> 00:03:34,752
Kuya Aga, come on, don’t say that.

55
00:03:34,777 --> 00:03:37,161
Looks like you’ve got something ready for…

56
00:03:38,860 --> 00:03:39,540
why are you crying?

57
00:03:39,565 --> 00:03:45,147
Wait, how are we going to recover
from this? Prices are so high now.

58
00:03:45,658 --> 00:03:48,575
Look at this expense.
Is this everything you spent?

59
00:03:48,729 --> 00:03:51,311
- Yes!
- Exactly! It’s expensive!

60
00:03:51,352 --> 00:03:55,393
How are we going to recover from this?
We’ll just sink deeper into debt.

61
00:03:55,418 --> 00:03:57,417
Well, everything’s more expensive now!

62
00:03:57,442 --> 00:03:58,442
Oh!

63
00:03:58,643 --> 00:04:00,030
I heard that!

64
00:04:00,787 --> 00:04:01,975
What does that mean?

65
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,944
You won’t be able to pay again?

66
00:04:03,969 --> 00:04:05,889
We’ll pay! Of course, it’s just tough.

67
00:04:05,914 --> 00:04:07,474
Look at these expenses!

68
00:04:07,721 --> 00:04:08,801
- It’s hard!
- That’s right.

69
00:04:09,238 --> 00:04:12,331
Hard or not, it’s not my problem!

70
00:04:12,537 --> 00:04:15,270
Debt is debt.

71
00:04:15,701 --> 00:04:18,474
We’ll pay, we’ll pay the debt!

72
00:04:18,499 --> 00:04:20,315
Why do you keep harping on debt?

73
00:04:20,340 --> 00:04:23,310
Debt, debt, debt! I’ll pay you back!

74
00:04:23,335 --> 00:04:24,565
Where? Where’s the payment?

75
00:04:24,711 --> 00:04:27,277
- I don’t see it!
- Just wait. Just wait, okay?

76
00:04:27,302 --> 00:04:28,157
That’s not okay.

77
00:04:28,182 --> 00:04:30,060
You’re acting like
you’re the one upset, but

78
00:04:30,084 --> 00:04:32,182
you’re the one who owes
money and isn’t paying!

79
00:04:32,207 --> 00:04:33,470
I’m not mad.

80
00:04:33,495 --> 00:04:36,023
I’m going to pay!
I’ll pay, but it’s just hard!

81
00:04:36,048 --> 00:04:37,761
Of course, I know my debt, okay?

82
00:04:37,786 --> 00:04:40,049
Kuya Aga, Iskineport…

83
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:42,427
- just relax!
- I’m not Iskineport!

84
00:04:43,513 --> 00:04:45,095
- I meant Tso K!
- Don’t change my name, okay?!

85
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:48,599
Tso K, Tso K! Relax!

86
00:04:48,624 --> 00:04:49,624
Don’t make me hurt you!

87
00:04:51,903 --> 00:04:55,122
2, and 3, and 4, and 5, and 6, and 7, 8!

88
00:04:55,147 --> 00:04:58,781
And 1, and 2, and 3, and
4, and 5, and 6, and 7, 8!

89
00:04:58,806 --> 00:05:02,754
And 1, and 2, and 3, and
4, and 5, and 6, and 7, 8!

90
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,620
- And 1, and 2, and 3, and 4,
- Tso K!

91
00:05:04,645 --> 00:05:06,677
And 5, and 6, and 7, one more!

92
00:05:06,702 --> 00:05:07,687
Tso K!

93
00:05:07,712 --> 00:05:08,712
Are you okay?

94
00:05:09,365 --> 00:05:10,339
Why?

95
00:05:10,364 --> 00:05:11,784
Do I not look okay?

96
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:14,986
The bread isn’t okay anymore!

97
00:05:17,012 --> 00:05:18,252
Ah… It’s nothing, it’s nothing.

98
00:05:18,717 --> 00:05:19,717
Don’t mind me!

99
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:22,572
I just had an argument with BFF.

100
00:05:24,269 --> 00:05:28,917
Wait a minute, what’s
that Zumbarangay thing…

101
00:05:29,452 --> 00:05:32,119
and they’re charging
fifty pesos for admission!

102
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,053
Ate Mariposa’s cellphone
shop isn’t doing well,

103
00:05:37,616 --> 00:05:39,869
so she thought of
organizing Zumba classes…

104
00:05:40,242 --> 00:05:41,296
with a small fee.

105
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:42,789
Lower, guys! Lower!

106
00:05:43,868 --> 00:05:45,208
See?! See that, see that?!

107
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:50,086
Those guys should be charged fifty pesos!

108
00:05:50,111 --> 00:05:51,713
Let’s see if she doesn’t get rich!

109
00:05:52,294 --> 00:05:55,827
Okay, guys! Good job!

110
00:05:56,722 --> 00:05:58,509
More, more, more!

111
00:05:58,664 --> 00:06:01,787
- See you next session!
- Ah, guys, you want more?

112
00:06:01,869 --> 00:06:03,836
- Yes!
- You want more?

113
00:06:03,861 --> 00:06:05,798
- Yes!
- Okay, ako magle-lead. Okay, I’ll lead.

114
00:06:05,984 --> 00:06:10,584
- No more! No more!
- No thanks?

115
00:06:11,796 --> 00:06:13,366
Alright, this is for you.

116
00:06:13,391 --> 00:06:16,236
Go back there and watch
over the rice store! Go!

117
00:06:16,829 --> 00:06:18,429
- Bye, guys!
- These people!

118
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:21,686
Anyway, hi Tso K!

119
00:06:22,086 --> 00:06:24,052
Do you want to join Zumba too?

120
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:30,728
You know, I can give you
private sessions for free!

121
00:06:30,972 --> 00:06:31,972
What?!

122
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:37,000
How many times do I
have to tell you, Mariposa?

123
00:06:37,574 --> 00:06:39,674
I’m not interested in you!

124
00:06:41,529 --> 00:06:44,095
Tso K, that’s too much!

125
00:06:44,823 --> 00:06:46,550
You’re being hurtful!

126
00:06:47,774 --> 00:06:48,774
Like I care?

127
00:06:49,108 --> 00:06:52,928
You’re ruining my already bad day!

128
00:06:53,816 --> 00:06:55,076
You’re unbelievable!

129
00:07:00,306 --> 00:07:01,306
Um, miss?

130
00:07:02,518 --> 00:07:03,685
Uh, hi!

131
00:07:04,613 --> 00:07:07,052
Do you also want to join Zumba, handsome?

132
00:07:08,063 --> 00:07:09,063
No, thanks!

133
00:07:09,747 --> 00:07:10,747
Hi, miss!

134
00:07:22,496 --> 00:07:23,932
Where's the ice, Bogs?

135
00:07:23,957 --> 00:07:24,957
Here it is!

136
00:07:27,453 --> 00:07:29,188
That’s guaranteed to be super cold!

137
00:07:29,213 --> 00:07:30,213
Oh, for sure!

138
00:07:35,593 --> 00:07:37,393
Hey, hurry up over there!

139
00:07:37,925 --> 00:07:39,119
Yes, Ma’am!

140
00:07:39,314 --> 00:07:41,687
Make sure nothing gets contaminated, okay?

141
00:07:42,026 --> 00:07:44,352
Our client from Spain is very particular!

142
00:07:44,914 --> 00:07:45,401
Yes, Ma’am!

143
00:07:45,426 --> 00:07:46,817
- Yes, Ma’am!
- Yes, ma’am, yes, ma’am!

144
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:47,841
What’s this?

145
00:07:48,107 --> 00:07:49,107
An organ?!

146
00:07:49,587 --> 00:07:51,977
You saw an organ and
thought, “organ for sale”? Really?!

147
00:07:53,689 --> 00:07:54,689
What is this?!

148
00:07:55,076 --> 00:07:56,489
Where’s Ben?

149
00:07:57,697 --> 00:07:58,697
Hold on.

150
00:08:04,622 --> 00:08:05,622
Hello?

151
00:08:05,957 --> 00:08:06,957
Hello, Ben?

152
00:08:07,272 --> 00:08:12,933
Have you found a prospect
for harvesting organs yet?

153
00:08:14,874 --> 00:08:17,994
Ma, it’s hard to find
someone with Spanish lineage.

154
00:08:18,434 --> 00:08:19,434
Hard?!

155
00:08:20,122 --> 00:08:22,535
Ben! Ben, focus!

156
00:08:23,525 --> 00:08:24,525
Remember,

157
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,259
we’re one of the big players in
the “Organs For Sale” syndicate,

158
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:31,798
and we’re already getting pressured
by powerful people in the black market.

159
00:08:31,823 --> 00:08:35,831
If we mess this
up, we’re done for!

160
00:08:36,934 --> 00:08:38,868
Okay, Ma, okay. I’ll handle it.

161
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:40,620
Oh, geez!

162
00:08:40,837 --> 00:08:41,837
What is this?!

163
00:08:44,017 --> 00:08:45,017
Driver!

164
00:08:46,094 --> 00:08:47,094
Where’s the driver?

165
00:08:50,448 --> 00:08:51,448
Driver!

166
00:08:53,145 --> 00:08:53,638
Ma’am?

167
00:08:53,791 --> 00:08:55,358
What are you doing there?!

168
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:58,177
Ma’am, it’s so hot in the van!

169
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:00,703
It’s cooler here!

170
00:09:00,728 --> 00:09:02,134
Get out of there!

171
00:09:05,444 --> 00:09:05,870
Hey!

172
00:09:05,895 --> 00:09:07,868
Make sure nothing gets contaminated, okay?

173
00:09:08,045 --> 00:09:09,565
That’s for the operations!

174
00:09:09,905 --> 00:09:11,305
- Yes, Ma’am.
- Ugh, so frustrating!

175
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,267
It hurts so much!

176
00:09:22,693 --> 00:09:26,033
Uncle K, my one and only!

177
00:09:26,774 --> 00:09:30,858
Mariposa, stop crying, stop crying.

178
00:09:38,842 --> 00:09:41,269
Um, Mariposa, right?

179
00:09:42,968 --> 00:09:43,508
Yes.

180
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:45,859
Stop crying. It doesn’t suit your beauty.

181
00:09:46,829 --> 00:09:47,943
Who are you?

182
00:09:48,362 --> 00:09:50,335
Don’t try to sweet-talk me.

183
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,735
I’m heartbroken!

184
00:09:57,006 --> 00:09:58,153
I’m Ben,

185
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:01,639
the guy who’ll never waste your love.

186
00:10:02,743 --> 00:10:03,743
Hmm?

187
00:10:04,364 --> 00:10:05,364
Whatever!

188
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:06,710
Hello!

189
00:10:06,735 --> 00:10:11,079
Oh, Boss Beauty, what happened to Mariposa?

190
00:10:11,117 --> 00:10:17,034
- Ate Cha!
- Why? What happened?

191
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:20,239
Well, Ate Cha, she’s broken!

192
00:10:20,557 --> 00:10:21,740
Broken-hearted because of Uncle K!

193
00:10:21,764 --> 00:10:22,317
What?!

194
00:10:22,348 --> 00:10:25,010
- Rejected.
- I’m broken-hearted!

195
00:10:25,944 --> 00:10:27,390
- I just don’t get it!
- Why?

196
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:31,722
With so many guys around
her, why would she fall for him?

197
00:10:31,808 --> 00:10:34,681
His looks are just…wow, unbelievable!

198
00:10:34,812 --> 00:10:35,799
What looks?!

199
00:10:35,824 --> 00:10:37,297
Ugly…if!

200
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:41,867
Ugly if you don’t
fall for Uncle K.

201
00:10:41,892 --> 00:10:46,060
Because, you know, he’s buff,
handsome, and his muscles!

202
00:10:46,601 --> 00:10:50,950
Wow, those muscles
are gym-built, seriously.

203
00:10:50,978 --> 00:10:53,605
He’s so handsome,
tons of girls are into him!

204
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,933
Boss Beauty! That was close, huh?

205
00:10:56,079 --> 00:10:57,439
Tso K, there you are!

206
00:10:57,477 --> 00:10:58,117
Yeah.

207
00:10:58,165 --> 00:10:59,992
For a second, I thought
you were Jay Manalo!

208
00:11:01,389 --> 00:11:03,862
You almost blew it! You almost did!

209
00:11:03,917 --> 00:11:07,530
Karl, look at Mariposa.

210
00:11:08,078 --> 00:11:10,678
She’s crying her eyes out! Poor thing!

211
00:11:10,703 --> 00:11:12,635
What am I supposed to do? What’s my fault?

212
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:14,847
I’m just being honest!

213
00:11:15,077 --> 00:11:23,077
Karl, there’s a right way to say
things without hurting anyone, right?

214
00:11:23,935 --> 00:11:29,165
Like before, when I told you that my
love and I got together, it didn’t hurt.

215
00:11:29,198 --> 00:11:31,508
I said it gently, didn’t I?

216
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:32,564
- Ow!
- Yeah!

217
00:11:32,586 --> 00:11:33,320
Gently?

218
00:11:33,345 --> 00:11:34,859
- Yeah!
- Not painful?

219
00:11:34,884 --> 00:11:36,652
Not painful! Just the right amount, right?

220
00:11:38,244 --> 00:11:40,744
My heart’s still bleeding
to this day, okay?!

221
00:11:40,769 --> 00:11:43,266
What did you say? Did you say something?

222
00:11:43,291 --> 00:11:43,985
No, nothing!

223
00:11:44,052 --> 00:11:44,439
Nothing?

224
00:11:44,464 --> 00:11:49,255
Nothing! I just said
fine, I’ll talk to her for you.

225
00:11:50,132 --> 00:11:53,379
- Please. Go ahead, please.
- Fine, Chacha!

226
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,447
Pretty please!

227
00:11:58,887 --> 00:12:01,154
Oh? Oh?

228
00:12:01,817 --> 00:12:03,777
She already replaced you?

229
00:12:03,802 --> 00:12:06,905
I thought you were
her one true love!

230
00:12:07,242 --> 00:12:08,242
Sorry!

231
00:12:08,377 --> 00:12:09,371
It’s okay!

232
00:12:09,396 --> 00:12:10,637
You too, Chacha?!

233
00:12:11,028 --> 00:12:12,555
Uh, no, Karl!

234
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:13,428
Never mind.

235
00:12:13,597 --> 00:12:14,757
Do what you want!

236
00:12:15,003 --> 00:12:16,583
Karl, Karl?!

237
00:12:16,609 --> 00:12:17,502
No, no!

238
00:12:17,586 --> 00:12:18,586
Just kidding!

239
00:12:19,721 --> 00:12:22,594
Oh, no, I’m in trouble now.

240
00:12:22,626 --> 00:12:24,595
- Bye, Ate Cha!
- I’m heading home! Bye-bye!

241
00:12:24,855 --> 00:12:26,675
It’s okay. I’m still here!

242
00:12:28,474 --> 00:12:29,494
Effective?

243
00:12:30,036 --> 00:12:31,789
He left! Effective! He’s gone, he left!

244
00:12:33,064 --> 00:12:34,131
He’s gone, he left!

245
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:43,958
Well, Uncle K better watch out
because I’ll make him super jealous.

246
00:12:47,724 --> 00:12:48,777
You’ll make him jealous?!

247
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:55,812
Oh, uh, no. I said don’t mess with
me because I get jealous easily. Right?

248
00:12:55,837 --> 00:12:56,313
Of course!

249
00:12:56,338 --> 00:12:58,046
You know that, right? Noted?

250
00:12:58,205 --> 00:13:00,105
I’m all yours, Mariposa.

251
00:13:07,254 --> 00:13:09,534
That’s it! Press this.

252
00:13:09,773 --> 00:13:10,773
It’s not pressing, see.

253
00:13:11,197 --> 00:13:14,209
- Is it not working?
- Orb, what are you doing?

254
00:13:14,938 --> 00:13:17,298
He’s testing his new wear tag.

255
00:13:17,482 --> 00:13:18,482
Look at that.

256
00:13:20,601 --> 00:13:21,601
Wear tag?

257
00:13:21,627 --> 00:13:22,627
What’s that?

258
00:13:23,092 --> 00:13:24,092
See this?

259
00:13:24,655 --> 00:13:26,868
Okay, put it in your pocket.

260
00:13:27,727 --> 00:13:29,434
- Then?
- Then walk away.

261
00:13:30,016 --> 00:13:31,275
- Walk away?
- Yeah!

262
00:13:31,355 --> 00:13:32,355
How far?

263
00:13:32,422 --> 00:13:33,422
Just keep going.

264
00:13:34,065 --> 00:13:35,632
- This far?
- Keep going!

265
00:13:35,864 --> 00:13:37,764
- Still?
- Farther. Keep going.

266
00:13:37,789 --> 00:13:38,789
Still?

267
00:13:39,015 --> 00:13:40,595
- Okay.
- Alright.

268
00:13:40,882 --> 00:13:42,008
Then?

269
00:13:45,635 --> 00:13:48,729
You’re one minute away from your wear tag.

270
00:13:49,068 --> 00:13:50,994
Hey! That’s cool!

271
00:13:51,019 --> 00:13:54,086
- Mmhmm! Yup!
- Wow! This is awesome!

272
00:13:54,111 --> 00:13:57,950
It’s like GPS; you can see
the location on your phone.

273
00:13:58,445 --> 00:14:01,146
So you can put it in
your bag, wallet, keys,

274
00:14:01,171 --> 00:14:04,456
or even on a person if
you want to track them.

275
00:14:04,581 --> 00:14:05,388
May I have this?

276
00:14:05,469 --> 00:14:07,936
Hey, hey, wait, wait, grandkids.

277
00:14:08,087 --> 00:14:09,707
That’s perfect for me!

278
00:14:10,045 --> 00:14:15,458
I need that because I always
forget where I put my stuff.

279
00:14:15,483 --> 00:14:16,387
Can I have one, please?

280
00:14:16,412 --> 00:14:18,842
Sure, Lola, here! This one’s for you!

281
00:14:19,192 --> 00:14:20,517
- That’s yours now!
- There you go!

282
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,434
I’ve got more anyway, so don’t worry.

283
00:14:22,504 --> 00:14:24,671
- I’ll put this in my bag, okay?
- Sure.

284
00:14:30,976 --> 00:14:32,669
- What’s wrong, Lola?
- Yes, lola?

285
00:14:33,662 --> 00:14:37,062
Help me out, I forgot where I put my bag.

286
00:14:40,077 --> 00:14:41,417
Lola!

287
00:14:41,779 --> 00:14:42,859
What’s so funny?

288
00:14:42,884 --> 00:14:44,510
Sorry, sorry!

289
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:48,707
One thousand three hundred,
divided by one thousand pieces…

290
00:14:50,082 --> 00:14:51,082
What’s this?

291
00:14:53,847 --> 00:14:55,480
One four three three.

292
00:14:56,613 --> 00:14:57,613
[Mom, Dad?]

293
00:14:58,403 --> 00:14:59,470
Take a break, guys!

294
00:14:59,516 --> 00:15:02,156
Take a break, you guys need coffee.

295
00:15:02,409 --> 00:15:03,382
- Have some coffee!
- For energy!

296
00:15:03,407 --> 00:15:06,081
Thanks, Atasha and Andres!

297
00:15:06,336 --> 00:15:07,909
You’re welcome!

298
00:15:07,934 --> 00:15:11,220
No, no, thank you. I’m just
surprised, kind of nervous…

299
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:12,148
It’s nothing.

300
00:15:12,173 --> 00:15:14,187
But the coffee came just in time

301
00:15:14,212 --> 00:15:20,394
because all this calculating
and budgeting is exhausting.

302
00:15:20,447 --> 00:15:22,423
But thank you so much, Andres, Atasha.

303
00:15:22,448 --> 00:15:23,448
That’s why!

304
00:15:23,793 --> 00:15:28,425
I rarely get to talk to you like
this, with everything going on lately.

305
00:15:28,450 --> 00:15:31,375
Yeah, you guys deserve
a break, so please enjoy!

306
00:15:31,444 --> 00:15:33,164
Thank you, thank you, thank you, thank you!

307
00:15:33,819 --> 00:15:35,259
- Let’s drink, my love!
- Try it now!

308
00:15:40,855 --> 00:15:42,575
She looks like she’s looking for something.

309
00:15:42,623 --> 00:15:44,829
Do you have Spanish ancestry?

310
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:49,281
Spanish? Oh, yes!
My great-great-grandfather.

311
00:15:52,789 --> 00:15:54,789
Ah…family medical history?

312
00:15:55,219 --> 00:15:56,326
Family—none.

313
00:15:56,539 --> 00:15:58,611
None of us are sick. None.

314
00:15:59,243 --> 00:16:03,086
Wait, wait, why are you
asking these questions?

315
00:16:03,321 --> 00:16:04,321
Who are you?

316
00:16:04,346 --> 00:16:06,692
Oh, I’m Minerva.

317
00:16:06,978 --> 00:16:09,222
Uh, I’m a surveyor for organs…

318
00:16:09,247 --> 00:16:09,702
Organs?

319
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:12,542
Nization…health organizations!

320
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:13,854
Organization!

321
00:16:13,885 --> 00:16:20,203
I’m surveying healthy individuals
for our free executive check-up!

322
00:16:20,228 --> 00:16:23,831
- Wow, free!
- Free! Sure, sure!

323
00:16:24,093 --> 00:16:24,700
Hey!

324
00:16:24,725 --> 00:16:28,249
That sounds good, especially
since it’s free. Big help.

325
00:16:29,098 --> 00:16:34,106
Who’s sponsoring all these
freebies in these hard times?

326
00:16:34,131 --> 00:16:36,210
I’ll definitely support
all these free programs!

327
00:16:36,235 --> 00:16:37,734
- Nothing to lose, right?
- Right?

328
00:16:37,759 --> 00:16:41,000
But is it really free?

329
00:16:41,393 --> 00:16:42,666
Oh, yes!

330
00:16:42,691 --> 00:16:44,774
And you’re definitely qualified!

331
00:16:45,307 --> 00:16:46,314
Qualified?!

332
00:16:46,584 --> 00:16:47,584
We are too?!

333
00:16:48,342 --> 00:16:48,989
Free check-up?!

334
00:16:49,204 --> 00:16:51,104
- Can we join? That’s great for us!
- Wait.

335
00:16:51,272 --> 00:16:53,820
Perfect! My throat’s been hurting lately!

336
00:16:53,868 --> 00:16:54,715
Throat?!

337
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:56,609
- Hold on, hold on.
- I can’t swallow properly!

338
00:16:56,674 --> 00:16:59,321
Do you have Spanish ancestry?

339
00:16:59,405 --> 00:17:01,805
Yes. I’m half Spanish.

340
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:03,475
And I’m half sardines.

341
00:17:03,514 --> 00:17:05,787
You’re joking again!

342
00:17:05,819 --> 00:17:06,819
Is it free?

343
00:17:07,161 --> 00:17:07,687
Oh, yes! It is!

344
00:17:07,745 --> 00:17:09,098
Hey, neighbors!

345
00:17:09,438 --> 00:17:10,651
Free check-up!

346
00:17:11,011 --> 00:17:13,011
- Come on, there’s free check-up here!
- Yes, free!

347
00:17:14,065 --> 00:17:15,065
Here it is!

348
00:17:15,864 --> 00:17:16,439
Ma’am!

349
00:17:16,464 --> 00:17:17,244
Yes?

350
00:17:17,277 --> 00:17:18,943
Ma’am, can I get a check-up too?

351
00:17:18,968 --> 00:17:19,968
Why?

352
00:17:19,993 --> 00:17:21,767
Are you feeling something?

353
00:17:22,182 --> 00:17:26,422
Um, not really. I just
feel like I’m a dragonfly.

354
00:17:29,919 --> 00:17:33,807
And 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5, 6, 7, 8.

355
00:17:33,877 --> 00:17:38,181
And 1, 2, and 3, and 4, other
side, and 5, 6, 7, one more time!

356
00:17:38,361 --> 00:17:42,915
1, 2, and 3, and 4, 5,
6, and 7, switch sides!

357
00:17:43,025 --> 00:17:45,131
2, 3, and 4, and shake it!

358
00:17:45,156 --> 00:17:46,129
- Tso K,
- Yeah?

359
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:49,023
Ate Mariposa really is
heart struck on you, huh?

360
00:17:49,423 --> 00:17:51,143
Huh? Heart struck?

361
00:17:51,262 --> 00:17:52,602
Maybe her head is struck!

362
00:17:53,679 --> 00:17:56,925
Plus, she already
likes someone else!

363
00:17:57,431 --> 00:17:58,885
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

364
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,760
You’re jealous, Tso K?

365
00:18:01,066 --> 00:18:02,066
Hey!

366
00:18:02,219 --> 00:18:04,186
- You’re jealous!
- Me, jealous over Mariposa?

367
00:18:04,312 --> 00:18:05,312
No way!

368
00:18:06,262 --> 00:18:10,114
If it were Chacha, then
yeah, I’d definitely be jealous!

369
00:18:10,894 --> 00:18:14,735
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

370
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,642
Okay, guys, perfect!

371
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:19,370
Let’s take a break!

372
00:18:20,136 --> 00:18:23,084
Just like how Tso K and I took a break!

373
00:18:23,213 --> 00:18:26,246
- Break?
- Sorry not sorry!

374
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:26,841
Break?

375
00:18:26,891 --> 00:18:28,352
You broke up? When were you even together?

376
00:18:28,376 --> 00:18:29,696
Look at her throwing shade at me!

377
00:18:31,097 --> 00:18:32,184
I’ll just stretch!

378
00:18:33,302 --> 00:18:35,276
Ugh, I don’t know what’s up with her!

379
00:18:37,362 --> 00:18:38,362
Ahem, ahem!

380
00:18:40,008 --> 00:18:45,076
- Oh my gosh! Hi, babes!
- Uh, babes? Babes!

381
00:18:45,101 --> 00:18:49,181
Babes, you’re so sweet!
You didn’t have to!

382
00:18:49,206 --> 00:18:50,976
Look, look!
Another hug, babes!

383
00:18:51,007 --> 00:18:53,866
There, see? All this “babes” nonsense!

384
00:18:53,891 --> 00:18:56,063
- Babe?
- And you said she doesn’t like me?

385
00:18:56,183 --> 00:18:57,332
What’s wrong with you, Tso K?

386
00:18:57,356 --> 00:18:58,623
Don’t you see it?

387
00:18:59,589 --> 00:19:01,364
My gosh, she’s just
trying to make you jealous!

388
00:19:01,388 --> 00:19:03,007
She might as well
shout your name!

389
00:19:03,032 --> 00:19:04,032
- Hmm?
- Yes!

390
00:19:04,253 --> 00:19:07,701
Oh my gosh, babes, feed me!
This is my favorite!

391
00:19:07,726 --> 00:19:10,403
How’d you know? Open it!

392
00:19:10,435 --> 00:19:11,875
- Uh, this is your favorite?
- Yes!

393
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:12,900
Okay, here, here!

394
00:19:16,343 --> 00:19:18,775
Hey! There’s still a peel on it!

395
00:19:19,704 --> 00:19:21,364
- Oh, sorry, sorry!
- Spit it out!

396
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:25,109
- It’s okay, babes!
- Did you like the flowers?

397
00:19:25,144 --> 00:19:27,451
Yes, they’re so pretty!

398
00:19:30,226 --> 00:19:33,019
By the way, I’d like to
invite you to my office later.

399
00:19:33,622 --> 00:19:36,642
I want to introduce you to my Mama Minerva.

400
00:19:36,839 --> 00:19:41,666
Oh, to your mom? You’re so sweet, babes!

401
00:19:41,691 --> 00:19:45,101
Unlike some people who just lead you on!

402
00:19:45,292 --> 00:19:47,292
- Oh!
- But…

403
00:19:47,362 --> 00:19:48,636
So…is it a yes?

404
00:19:48,661 --> 00:19:51,463
Ah, yes! It’s a yes for me!

405
00:19:53,473 --> 00:19:56,593
Boss Beauty, your friend
isn’t just average, huh?

406
00:19:56,632 --> 00:20:04,632
You know, Tso K, this friend
of mine, not just average.

407
00:20:06,042 --> 00:20:07,702
Absolutely not.

408
00:20:08,684 --> 00:20:10,477
Ah, babes, let’s take a selfie first.

409
00:20:10,502 --> 00:20:11,357
There!

410
00:20:11,382 --> 00:20:12,382
Let’s take a selfie!

411
00:20:14,053 --> 00:20:15,053
Okay.

412
00:20:42,123 --> 00:20:43,717
Ma, I don’t want to do this anymore.

413
00:20:44,558 --> 00:20:45,558
I’m in love.

414
00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:49,090
I want to live a normal life.

415
00:20:49,454 --> 00:20:50,994
I want to work an honest job.

416
00:20:51,553 --> 00:20:53,980
In fact, I’m planning
to introduce her to you.

417
00:20:55,039 --> 00:20:58,232
Aww, my child!

418
00:21:00,236 --> 00:21:01,356
Does she have good kidneys?

419
00:21:01,609 --> 00:21:02,609
Ma…

420
00:21:02,848 --> 00:21:04,601
I’m just kidding!

421
00:21:06,456 --> 00:21:08,016
Son, you know how it is.

422
00:21:08,552 --> 00:21:12,446
Exiting the syndicate isn’t easy.

423
00:21:13,218 --> 00:21:17,812
But if that’s what
you want, fine.

424
00:21:18,647 --> 00:21:23,563
I’ll let you go, but finish all our
pending contracts first, okay?

425
00:21:24,470 --> 00:21:26,617
Alright, Ma. But after this,

426
00:21:27,410 --> 00:21:29,170
Mariposa and I are
done with this life, okay?

427
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:29,897
Hmm, fine.

428
00:21:29,922 --> 00:21:36,234
But make sure you help me find other
kidneys for the rest of our contracts.

429
00:21:37,540 --> 00:21:38,540
Ma, perfect timing!

430
00:21:39,073 --> 00:21:40,866
She’s with her Zumba buddies now.

431
00:21:40,891 --> 00:21:44,012
I’m sure their organs are fit and healthy!

432
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:50,303
Just promise me, Ma,
after this, we’re out of here.

433
00:21:50,328 --> 00:21:51,328
Alright!

434
00:21:51,865 --> 00:21:55,082
Actually, while you’re at it…

435
00:21:55,174 --> 00:22:01,274
Grab the bakery owner
from Barangay Singko too.

436
00:22:01,359 --> 00:22:03,279
Take her husband and kid along.

437
00:22:04,172 --> 00:22:05,399
Perfect timing!

438
00:22:05,547 --> 00:22:07,467
They have Spanish blood.

439
00:22:08,106 --> 00:22:11,846
Their organs are compatible
with our clients in Spain!

440
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:16,460
Are—are you sure they
have Spanish blood, Ma?

441
00:22:17,757 --> 00:22:19,291
What?! Are you questioning me?

442
00:22:19,659 --> 00:22:21,805
Hmm! Have I ever been wrong?

443
00:22:22,805 --> 00:22:25,191
Hurry up! Doc is on his way!

444
00:22:25,216 --> 00:22:28,286
You know how he is—he
just wants to cut and go!

445
00:22:28,499 --> 00:22:29,945
- Alright, Ma.
- Go, go! Hurry!

446
00:22:39,346 --> 00:22:40,773
Does he look like he’s Spanish?

447
00:22:42,045 --> 00:22:44,205
Looks more like
burnt Spanish bread!

448
00:22:48,143 --> 00:22:51,537
So good! There’s blood and intestines!

449
00:22:52,669 --> 00:22:54,615
You can eat those! Go ahead!

450
00:22:55,337 --> 00:22:56,484
Wait a minute, Tso K!

451
00:22:57,774 --> 00:22:59,084
- Here it is.
- What’s that?

452
00:22:59,122 --> 00:23:02,570
I need to give it to Andres.
He left his wear tag with me.

453
00:23:03,315 --> 00:23:06,348
Don’t worry about it.
I already told him to come here.

454
00:23:07,410 --> 00:23:08,410
- Oh!
- He’ll be here!

455
00:23:08,945 --> 00:23:09,698
Alright then.

456
00:23:09,810 --> 00:23:10,990
This one looks tastier!

457
00:23:15,938 --> 00:23:16,938
Hey, someone’s buying!

458
00:23:17,257 --> 00:23:19,364
- Hey! Wait a second, why?!
- Hold on, hold on!

459
00:23:19,389 --> 00:23:22,049
- Get in! Get in!
- Grab them, grab them!

460
00:23:23,009 --> 00:23:24,009
Wait, where...

461
00:23:24,135 --> 00:23:27,234
Bring that girl too! Hurry up!

462
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,780
Move faster, faster!

463
00:23:31,975 --> 00:23:33,748
It looks like someone…

464
00:23:34,272 --> 00:23:36,432
- Wait a second!
- Hey! Hey!

465
00:23:36,603 --> 00:23:37,603
Hey!

466
00:23:38,122 --> 00:23:39,122
- Hey!
- Hey!

467
00:23:40,597 --> 00:23:43,397
- That’s Chef K and the others!
- Andres, they kidnapped Orb and Tso K!

468
00:23:43,583 --> 00:23:46,003
They were kidnapped!
They might do something bad to Orb!

469
00:23:46,804 --> 00:23:51,829
I’ve got an idea! Let’s
tell Kuya Aga! Your dad!

470
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:54,692
- No! I’ve got an idea!
- What?!

471
00:23:55,157 --> 00:23:58,017
Let’s tell your dad, Kuya Aga!

472
00:23:58,303 --> 00:23:58,850
Really?

473
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,249
Yes! Ouch!

474
00:24:00,274 --> 00:24:03,317
That’s exactly what I said! You’re
just repeating me! Come on, let’s go!

475
00:24:03,342 --> 00:24:05,066
- Let’s go!
- Let’s go now!

476
00:24:13,607 --> 00:24:16,987
Oh my gosh, what kind of place is this?!

477
00:24:17,417 --> 00:24:19,710
It looks like a warehouse!

478
00:24:20,097 --> 00:24:21,097
Where are we?

479
00:24:21,327 --> 00:24:23,834
This is where Ben told us to go!

480
00:24:23,997 --> 00:24:26,768
I think it’s their
office. It’s huge, right?

481
00:24:27,021 --> 00:24:28,268
- Office?!
- Yes.

482
00:24:28,314 --> 00:24:29,454
This is what an
office looks like?!

483
00:24:29,478 --> 00:24:31,122
- What the—
- Keep walking! Keep walking!

484
00:24:31,977 --> 00:24:34,317
Don’t push me! Why are you shoving?!

485
00:24:34,385 --> 00:24:35,659
Walk, walk!

486
00:24:36,214 --> 00:24:39,079
I am walking! Stop shoving me already!

487
00:24:39,104 --> 00:24:41,033
Tso K? Tso K!

488
00:24:41,148 --> 00:24:44,148
I knew you’d come looking for me!

489
00:24:44,173 --> 00:24:45,893
Why are you here? What are you doing here?!

490
00:24:45,944 --> 00:24:47,499
This is Ben’s office!

491
00:24:47,524 --> 00:24:48,524
Uh, yeah…

492
00:24:49,552 --> 00:24:53,047
Be—? No, I wasn’t looking for you!

493
00:24:53,586 --> 00:24:59,113
Oh, stop pretending.
I knew you’d follow me!

494
00:24:59,138 --> 00:25:01,582
Why would I follow you?
I wasn’t following you!

495
00:25:02,169 --> 00:25:03,369
We were kidnapped!

496
00:25:03,597 --> 00:25:04,597
What?

497
00:25:04,943 --> 00:25:05,943
Huh? Is that true?

498
00:25:06,216 --> 00:25:07,296
Did you really kidnap them?

499
00:25:08,007 --> 00:25:08,680
Is that true?

500
00:25:08,740 --> 00:25:10,333
Yes, Ate Mariposa.

501
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:13,113
They grabbed us and shoved us into a van.

502
00:25:13,565 --> 00:25:13,832
That’s right!

503
00:25:13,857 --> 00:25:17,964
Isn’t that what’s been on the news?
They kidnap people and sell their organs?!

504
00:25:17,989 --> 00:25:19,168
- What?!
- Organs?!

505
00:25:19,657 --> 00:25:20,657
Exactly!

506
00:25:21,536 --> 00:25:22,536
Who are they?!

507
00:25:22,571 --> 00:25:24,225
Wow, you’re smart, girl!

508
00:25:24,502 --> 00:25:25,502
Thank you!

509
00:25:26,176 --> 00:25:28,370
Wait, who are these people?!

510
00:25:30,025 --> 00:25:31,225
Aren’t they the bakery owners?

511
00:25:31,437 --> 00:25:32,957
The other bakery!

512
00:25:33,044 --> 00:25:34,251
The Pers family!

513
00:25:34,655 --> 00:25:35,961
Oh! That’s them!

514
00:25:36,151 --> 00:25:39,968
But why take us? Why not Aga?!

515
00:25:40,142 --> 00:25:40,769
Not me!

516
00:25:40,888 --> 00:25:42,055
Psst! Hey, shut up!

517
00:25:42,587 --> 00:25:44,247
Tie them up! Start with the loud one!

518
00:25:44,272 --> 00:25:46,622
W-why tie us up so fast? Why tie us?

519
00:25:46,842 --> 00:25:49,392
- Hurry up, hurry up!
- I’m not loud, I swear! Hold on a second.

520
00:25:49,466 --> 00:25:55,235
Wait, wait! I’m not loud! Look, I’ll
be quiet now. See? Mouth zipped!

521
00:25:56,369 --> 00:25:57,369
Shut up!

522
00:26:01,883 --> 00:26:04,378
Ugh, I really need a check-up.

523
00:26:04,492 --> 00:26:05,635
Mom! Dad!

524
00:26:05,778 --> 00:26:06,740
What?!

525
00:26:06,765 --> 00:26:07,473
What is it?!

526
00:26:07,512 --> 00:26:08,245
What now?!

527
00:26:08,270 --> 00:26:08,883
Oh, sorry!

528
00:26:08,922 --> 00:26:10,160
- Ow!
- Sorry, let’s go!

529
00:26:10,450 --> 00:26:11,298
What? Why?!

530
00:26:11,323 --> 00:26:12,603
What’s happening?

531
00:26:12,628 --> 00:26:14,323
- Anne and Tso K were kidnapped!
- Yes!

532
00:26:14,349 --> 00:26:15,063
What?!

533
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:18,728
Wait, wait, wait…time
out, time out, time out!

534
00:26:18,916 --> 00:26:21,929
Anne and Tso K were kidnapped?!

535
00:26:22,057 --> 00:26:24,310
Yes, Kuya! We saw it happen!

536
00:26:24,336 --> 00:26:25,116
Where were they taken?!

537
00:26:25,156 --> 00:26:28,590
Hold on! Wait! I gave Anne the wear tag!

538
00:26:28,615 --> 00:26:29,295
She has a wear tag?

539
00:26:29,328 --> 00:26:30,328
Yeah, she has a wear tag!

540
00:26:30,550 --> 00:26:31,470
Wait! Let me check!

541
00:26:31,495 --> 00:26:32,503
Wear tag, then what?

542
00:26:32,588 --> 00:26:35,191
It’s like a GPS to track the location.

543
00:26:35,225 --> 00:26:36,845
Iskineport…we should…

544
00:26:36,921 --> 00:26:38,628
Here, here! Dad, look at this!

545
00:26:39,101 --> 00:26:41,001
There! Good thing Andres thought of it!

546
00:26:41,722 --> 00:26:42,546
Here, here it is!

547
00:26:42,586 --> 00:26:43,034
I didn’t see it earlier!

548
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:43,961
That’s the point of the wear tag!

549
00:26:43,994 --> 00:26:45,236
Well, we didn’t see where they took them.

550
00:26:45,260 --> 00:26:46,877
But look, you can see it here! It’s a
good thing they have the wear tag!

551
00:26:46,901 --> 00:26:48,247
Alright, let’s go! Let’s go now!

552
00:26:48,289 --> 00:26:50,322
Come on! Let’s go!

553
00:26:50,786 --> 00:26:52,140
Lola Maxi, Lola Maxi! Come with us!

554
00:26:52,164 --> 00:26:53,293
Lola Maxi, come with us!

555
00:26:53,349 --> 00:26:56,010
I don’t want to! I need to pee!

556
00:26:56,545 --> 00:26:57,545
You need to pee?

557
00:26:57,833 --> 00:26:58,500
Let’s go! Come on!

558
00:26:58,673 --> 00:27:01,100
Are you getting a UTI?
Peeing all the time! Let’s go!

559
00:27:05,095 --> 00:27:08,055
You’re unbelievable! Now I’m caught
up in this too! Ben’s a syndicate?!

560
00:27:08,783 --> 00:27:10,233
I didn’t know!

561
00:27:10,695 --> 00:27:12,322
Well, you should’ve known right away!

562
00:27:12,540 --> 00:27:15,260
Now we’re caught up in this mess!
Aga should be the one here! Not us!

563
00:27:21,536 --> 00:27:22,536
Be quiet!

564
00:27:24,470 --> 00:27:25,347
There they are!

565
00:27:25,399 --> 00:27:26,955
- Sshh!
- Quiet down!

566
00:27:27,391 --> 00:27:28,796
Alright, let’s charge in!

567
00:27:28,821 --> 00:27:29,557
Hey!

568
00:27:29,582 --> 00:27:31,565
- Orb!
- Andres! Tash!

569
00:27:31,604 --> 00:27:32,604
Hey, hey, hey!

570
00:27:32,633 --> 00:27:33,338
Iskineport!

571
00:27:33,376 --> 00:27:35,432
Let’s escape! Let’s
escape! Don’t make a sound!

572
00:27:36,348 --> 00:27:39,468
Tash, Tash! Help me first, Tash! Looks
like Anne’s the only one you’re helping!

573
00:27:40,149 --> 00:27:41,255
It’s Orb’s fault!

574
00:27:41,452 --> 00:27:42,211
Be quiet!

575
00:27:42,241 --> 00:27:43,347
You’re amazing!

576
00:27:43,372 --> 00:27:44,501
Sssh, ssh! Be quiet!

577
00:27:44,535 --> 00:27:46,313
- Thank you, Orb!
- Thank you, take a rest!

578
00:27:46,747 --> 00:27:49,069
- That stings! It stings!
- I knew it!

579
00:27:50,281 --> 00:27:51,295
There, there!

580
00:27:51,409 --> 00:27:51,904
It hurts!

581
00:27:52,251 --> 00:27:52,894
Are you okay?

582
00:27:52,919 --> 00:27:55,061
I’m fine, even though you
didn’t really want to help me out!

583
00:27:55,085 --> 00:27:56,124
Don’t make a sound, they might hear us!

584
00:27:56,148 --> 00:27:57,872
- All good now!
- Sshhh!

585
00:27:58,072 --> 00:27:59,677
You’re the best! Thank you so much!

586
00:27:59,723 --> 00:28:02,629
Tash, thank you! You’re the best!

587
00:28:05,332 --> 00:28:10,694
Ah! Sometimes you just get lucky!

588
00:28:11,505 --> 00:28:14,891
I thought I wouldn’t catch the Pers family!

589
00:28:15,161 --> 00:28:17,066
Luck really is on my side!

590
00:28:17,552 --> 00:28:20,566
You know, the police are on
their way. You’re all going to jail!

591
00:28:20,604 --> 00:28:21,819
- What?!
- Perfect!

592
00:28:21,862 --> 00:28:23,415
What?! Wait, wait!

593
00:28:23,467 --> 00:28:26,776
Before the cops arrive, we
need to harvest their organs!

594
00:28:28,179 --> 00:28:29,179
Mom!

595
00:28:29,301 --> 00:28:31,925
I won’t let you hurt
them, especially Mariposa!

596
00:28:32,033 --> 00:28:32,890
What?

597
00:28:32,928 --> 00:28:34,443
- He says you, Mariposa!
- He said Mariposa!

598
00:28:34,467 --> 00:28:35,419
But we need to!

599
00:28:35,479 --> 00:28:38,631
Hey! Don’t worry!
I’ll take care of them!

600
00:28:39,001 --> 00:28:41,557
Save yourselves, I’ll handle this!

601
00:28:41,787 --> 00:28:43,325
I don’t understand what you’re saying!

602
00:28:43,604 --> 00:28:45,466
I’ll take care of it, Chef K.

603
00:28:45,549 --> 00:28:50,711
Wait! These two troublemakers!
Quickly, deal with them!

604
00:28:50,930 --> 00:28:53,821
- Hey! Hey! Hey!
- Why is it always me?! Ow, ow, ow!

605
00:28:54,539 --> 00:28:57,174
Keep going!

606
00:29:01,025 --> 00:29:04,242
Hey! Why are you giving them up?!

607
00:29:04,668 --> 00:29:06,971
- They’re pitiful!
- They’re hurting!

608
00:29:13,274 --> 00:29:18,531
[cheers]

609
00:29:18,738 --> 00:29:20,257
Take them! Take those guys!

610
00:29:20,283 --> 00:29:21,078
Take them! Take them!

611
00:29:21,149 --> 00:29:23,749
Kuya! I’m all beaten up! Kuya,
good thing you’re here, I’m a mess!

612
00:29:26,815 --> 00:29:27,820
Take them! Take them!

613
00:29:32,182 --> 00:29:33,182
Right!

614
00:29:33,948 --> 00:29:36,720
Take this! Chief! Hurry!

615
00:29:37,472 --> 00:29:38,091
Why, Sir?

616
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:39,321
You forgot the other two!

617
00:29:39,423 --> 00:29:40,185
Oh, really?

618
00:29:40,215 --> 00:29:41,082
Take them!

619
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,120
Come on, come with me!

620
00:29:49,697 --> 00:29:52,805
Chief! Not this one! Those two!

621
00:29:53,882 --> 00:29:55,491
Those two! Take them!

622
00:29:56,957 --> 00:29:57,957
Take them!

623
00:29:58,866 --> 00:30:00,019
I helped earlier!

624
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:01,523
Serves you right!

625
00:30:01,548 --> 00:30:02,268
Bye-bye!

626
00:30:02,295 --> 00:30:03,695
- These cops are amazing!
- Bye-bye!

627
00:30:04,176 --> 00:30:05,176
Amazing, amazing!

628
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:09,831
- Oh, wait a second! Wait, wait, wait!
- Oh, oh, oh, oh!

629
00:30:09,856 --> 00:30:11,340
Tso K, Tso K!

630
00:30:11,731 --> 00:30:12,821
BFF, you’re sweating!

631
00:30:13,134 --> 00:30:13,992
I don’t like getting angry!

632
00:30:14,129 --> 00:30:16,119
Your sweat is cold! So cold!

633
00:30:16,189 --> 00:30:18,389
- Don’t… I’m not talking to you!
- It’s so cold!

634
00:30:18,434 --> 00:30:20,734
This is the only time I’ll thank you, BFF!

635
00:30:21,594 --> 00:30:22,646
Thank you so much!

636
00:30:23,528 --> 00:30:26,632
- But it’s so hot here!
- Yeah, it’s hot!

637
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:29,009
Of all the places to go,
we end up in a warehouse!

638
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:30,186
Exactly, let’s go!

639
00:30:30,257 --> 00:30:30,671
Where to?

640
00:30:31,168 --> 00:30:32,120
Let’s head to Baguio!

641
00:30:32,189 --> 00:30:33,836
- What?!
- Baguio?!

642
00:30:33,863 --> 00:30:35,692
Yay!

643
00:30:35,815 --> 00:30:37,449
Field trip!

644
00:30:37,742 --> 00:30:40,309
Baguio! Baguio! Baguio! Baguio!

645
00:30:40,334 --> 00:30:42,612
Look at us now! We're all safe!

646
00:30:42,699 --> 00:30:44,685
Nothing bad happened to us!

647
00:30:45,026 --> 00:30:46,822
Well, lesson learned.

648
00:30:46,913 --> 00:30:49,151
We shouldn’t trust people so easily!

649
00:30:49,677 --> 00:30:52,792
And good thing I bought
that wear tracker for Orb,

650
00:30:53,057 --> 00:30:55,023
so we could track them down, right?

651
00:30:55,962 --> 00:30:58,714
Really? You actually bought this for me?

652
00:30:58,954 --> 00:31:02,311
Ah, I mean...

653
00:31:02,338 --> 00:31:04,795
Aaahhh, huli!

654
00:31:04,826 --> 00:31:07,226
The tracker I bought that
you ended up with, remember?

655
00:31:07,290 --> 00:31:10,071
Is that true?

656
00:31:10,413 --> 00:31:11,994
Anyway, thanks, Orb!

657
00:31:14,629 --> 00:31:16,843
It’s so hot in here. I can’t take it!

658
00:31:16,877 --> 00:31:18,691
It really is scorching!

659
00:31:18,716 --> 00:31:21,023
Wait, wait a second.
Why does it seem like...

660
00:31:21,048 --> 00:31:22,640
Oh, the mother-in-law
reacted right away to that!

661
00:31:22,664 --> 00:31:23,750
- No...
- Just kidding, just kidding!

662
00:31:23,774 --> 00:31:25,479
No, I was just looking at Mariposa.

663
00:31:25,504 --> 00:31:29,313
She still seems sad even now.

664
00:31:30,144 --> 00:31:31,882
Well, of course.

665
00:31:31,907 --> 00:31:34,722
She got blinded by a guy’s looks.

666
00:31:35,212 --> 00:31:37,127
She liked someone handsome,

667
00:31:37,173 --> 00:31:43,697
but she didn’t know that not all
handsome guys are good people.

668
00:31:43,729 --> 00:31:45,601
Do you know anyone like that?

669
00:31:45,770 --> 00:31:46,575
I do!

670
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,415
Who? Who?

671
00:31:47,443 --> 00:31:48,443
Never mind!

672
00:31:50,059 --> 00:31:51,983
I might disappear if I tell you!

673
00:31:53,452 --> 00:31:55,256
But seriously, don’t be like that.

674
00:31:55,285 --> 00:31:58,399
Now you miss Tso K because of it, right?

675
00:31:59,192 --> 00:32:00,192
Yes!

676
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:00,975
Ahem!

677
00:32:01,061 --> 00:32:02,080
Whoa, intense!

678
00:32:02,105 --> 00:32:03,105
Ahem!

679
00:32:04,385 --> 00:32:05,107
Ahem!

680
00:32:05,399 --> 00:32:07,537
Oh, Tso K.

681
00:32:07,742 --> 00:32:08,742
Yeah?

682
00:32:08,796 --> 00:32:10,973
I just want to tell you that.

683
00:32:11,601 --> 00:32:14,478
I’m sorry I made you jealous.

684
00:32:14,715 --> 00:32:15,715
Oh no!

685
00:32:15,893 --> 00:32:18,903
I’m sorry for hurting you.

686
00:32:19,226 --> 00:32:20,226
Yeah!

687
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:21,182
Tso K...

688
00:32:21,207 --> 00:32:21,957
Looking good, huh?

689
00:32:21,995 --> 00:32:23,738
I just want to tell you that

690
00:32:24,544 --> 00:32:26,644
you’re still my one and only!

691
00:32:27,583 --> 00:32:31,712
Yeah, Mariposa, I just
want to tell you again.

692
00:32:31,889 --> 00:32:35,554
I might’ve told you before
that you’re not my type.

693
00:32:36,797 --> 00:32:39,811
But that doesn’t mean I
don’t like you as a person.

694
00:32:40,978 --> 00:32:42,578
I like you for who you are.

695
00:32:42,623 --> 00:32:45,394
And honestly, I don’t blame you.

696
00:32:46,163 --> 00:32:47,639
It’s not new to me.

697
00:32:49,014 --> 00:32:51,523
A lot of people like me...

698
00:32:51,935 --> 00:32:54,638
tall, dark, and handsome.

699
00:32:54,663 --> 00:32:55,148
- What?
- Hmm?

700
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:55,967
- What?
- Handsome?

701
00:32:56,002 --> 00:32:58,413
And I also want to say... Can I
place my hand on your shoulder?

702
00:32:58,437 --> 00:32:59,594
Of course, Tso K!

703
00:32:59,750 --> 00:33:01,284
I just want to tell you

704
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:06,272
that you can’t always
get everything you want.

705
00:33:07,718 --> 00:33:10,499
Sometimes, others take it from you.

706
00:33:19,418 --> 00:33:22,518
That’s just how life goes.

707
00:33:22,897 --> 00:33:26,854
But you’re okay with me.
It’s just... well, that’s how it is.

708
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:28,740
You’re okay, Mariposa.

709
00:33:29,954 --> 00:33:32,016
No matter what you say, Tso K,

710
00:33:32,617 --> 00:33:34,507
I’ll still wait for you!

711
00:33:35,846 --> 00:33:37,070
Wait for me still?

712
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,607
That’s enough, that’s enough!

713
00:33:38,632 --> 00:33:41,196
You’re really patient,
huh? Hey, hey! None of that!

714
00:33:41,986 --> 00:33:42,946
Oh, no kissing, no kissing!

715
00:33:42,989 --> 00:33:44,551
Sorry, sorry, I got carried away.

716
00:33:44,583 --> 00:33:47,893
Oh, you got carried away, huh?
You don’t even like his looks!

717
00:33:47,917 --> 00:33:48,375
What?

718
00:33:48,757 --> 00:33:49,933
You said that earlier, right?

719
00:33:49,958 --> 00:33:51,017
No, I didn’t say anything earlier!

720
00:33:51,041 --> 00:33:52,801
- You did! You said it!
- That came from you!

721
00:33:53,162 --> 00:33:53,952
No, I have something to tell you.

722
00:33:53,980 --> 00:33:54,980
What?

723
00:33:55,310 --> 00:33:56,143
Is it important?

724
00:33:56,188 --> 00:33:58,726
It is! It’s important!
They know it. Here it is...

725
00:34:00,584 --> 00:34:02,755
In struggles and joy,

726
00:34:03,494 --> 00:34:07,289
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!

727
00:34:08,318 --> 00:34:09,813
Let’s play spirit of the glass!

728
00:34:10,526 --> 00:34:11,812
What do you think?!

729
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:12,313
Up to you!

730
00:34:12,338 --> 00:34:13,338
Cowards!

731
00:34:15,695 --> 00:34:18,662
Maxi, you’re more
beautiful than the morning!

732
00:34:18,737 --> 00:34:19,937
Are you here to borrow money?

733
00:34:20,041 --> 00:34:21,831
I can’t help but notice your beauty!

734
00:34:22,566 --> 00:34:24,766
I am the messenger!

735
00:34:24,831 --> 00:34:27,036
And the messenger has a message!

736
00:34:27,061 --> 00:34:28,697
There’s a miracle!

737
00:34:28,791 --> 00:34:30,957
I’m talking to my Daddy hunk!

738
00:34:31,126 --> 00:34:32,798
What’s happening to you, BFF?

739
00:34:32,823 --> 00:34:36,422
Come closer, and I’ll whisper!

740
00:34:37,726 --> 00:34:38,206
Hey!

741
00:34:38,275 --> 00:34:40,503
You’re possessed, BFF, you’re possessed!

742
00:34:40,873 --> 00:34:42,192
That hurts, you know!

743
00:34:42,397 --> 00:34:45,273
I am Ted Pakipot! Three are possessed.

744
00:34:45,582 --> 00:34:46,582
- Oh no!
- Hey!

745
00:34:47,472 --> 00:34:49,443
- Ah, a ghost!
- Ah!

746
00:34:51,262 --> 00:34:52,271
What is this?!
